ts are in themselves the ruin of representation as a whole, and the text is illustrated with Kelly's art. This original and provocative account of Deleuze contributes significantly to a critical feminist politics and philosophy, as well as to an understanding of feminist art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFeminism and art. 0aPsychoanalysis and art. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aart.  aartist.  aartistic.  achange.  acreation.  acreative.  afeminism.  afeminist art.  afeminist politics.  afeminist studies.  afeminist.  afrench philosopher.  afrench thinker.  agovernment.  agreat thinkers.  ahierarchic.  ahierarchy.  aillustrated.  alaw and order.  aphilosopher.  aphilosophy of difference.  aphilosophy.  apolitical.  apolitics.  arepresentation.  asocial change.  asocial history.  asocial studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092223540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922235423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520922235/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY